and we don't have to worry about it getting too large. That's a real-world modularity concept.",[12,651,652],{},"Now that we've got modularity down, let's look at the differences between CommonJS and ES Modules.",[20,654,656],{"id":655},"commonjs","CommonJS",[12,658,659],{},"I mentioned CommonJS came about as Node.js's solution for modularity, so we have to know it.",[12,661,662,663,666,667,670,671,673],{},"CommonJS is easy to use — basically ",[88,664,665],{},"require"," paired with ",[88,668,669],{},"module.exports"," or ",[88,672,590],{},". We've already shown this in the previous example, so let's just recall it:",[81,675,676],{"className":83,"code":337,"language":85,"meta":86,"style":86},[88,677,678,682,688,694,700,706,720,724,744,764],{"__ignoreMap":86},[91,679,680],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,681,98],{"class":97},[91,683,684,686],{"class":93,"line":101},[91,685,105],{"class":104},[91,687,134],{"class":115},[91,689,690,692],{"class":93,"line":137},[91,691,354],{"class":274},[91,693,357],{"class":115},[91,695,696,698],{"class":93,"line":152},[91,697,362],{"class":274},[91,699,357],{"class":115},[91,701,702,704],{"class":93,"line":158},[91,703,369],{"class":274},[91,705,357],{"class":115},[91,707,708,710,712,714,716,718],{"class":93,"line":165},[91,709,376],{"class":115},[91,711,379],{"class":104},[91,713,382],{"class":108},[91,715,266],{"class":115},[91,717,388],{"class":387},[91,719,391],{"class":115},[91,721,722],{"class":93,"line":189},[91,723,162],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":161},[91,725,726,728,730,732,734,736,738,740,742],{"class":93,"line":201},[91,727,260],{"class":115},[91,729,263],{"class":108},[91,731,266],{"class":115},[91,733,269],{"class":108},[91,735,266],{"class":115},[91,737,275],{"class":274},[91,739,122],{"class":115},[91,741,280],{"class":274},[91,743,283],{"class":115},[91,745,746,748,750,752,754,756,758,760,762],{"class":93,"line":206},[91,747,260],{"class":115},[91,749,263],{"class":108},[91,751,266],{"class":115},[91,753,295],{"class":108},[9